arning%20under%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanders.senate.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2FSecure-Retirement-for-All-Report-02.28.2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Sen.%20Bernie%20Sanders%20published%20in%20March%20and%20based%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrr.bc.edu%2Fthe-national-retirement-risk-index-version-2-0%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENational%20Retirement%20Risk%20Index%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20retirement%20accounts%20are%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-benefits-offered-by-employers-boosts-worker-productivity-retention-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompany%20benefit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20employees%20can%20choose%20to%20contribute%20some%20of%20their%20paychecks%20to%20throughout%20their%20careers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-australia-no-regrets-cheaper-sunshine-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAustralia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20requires%20that%20employers%20make%20regular%20contributions%20to%20a%20retirement%20fund%20for%20each%20employee%20%E2%80%94%20a%20system%20called%20superannuation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Reilly%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20financial%20research%20firm%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETIAA%20Institute%20and%20a%20non-resident%20scholar%20at%20Georgetown%20University's%20Center%20for%20Retirement%20Initiatives%2C%20said%20Australia's%20system%20makes%20sure%20all%20adults%20have%20a%20retirement%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20is%20put%20into%20a%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhereas%20in%20the%20US%2C%20you%20only%20get%20put%20into%20a%20plan%20if%20you'd%20work%20for%20an%20employer%20that%20offers%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeventy-one%20percent%20of%20nonretired%20Americans%20said%20they%20are%20at%20least%20moderately%20worried%20about%20being%20able%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-money-do-i-need-for-retirement-gen-x-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efund%20their%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F506330%2Famericans-outlook-retirement-worsened.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201%2C013%20US%20adults%20in%20April%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReilly%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20there%20are%20structural%20differences%20in%20how%20America%20and%20Australia%20handle%20savings%20for%20older%20adults.%20And%20while%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eit%20may%20be%20tough%20to%20implement%20Australia's%20system%20halfway%20around%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20US%20could%20get%20close%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAustralian%20retirement%20system%20puts%20saving%20responsibility%20on%20employers%2C%20not%20employees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20current%20retirement%20infrastructure%20includes%20two%20major%20categories%3A%20defined%20contribution%20plans%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDefined%20contribution%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-401k-isnt-working-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20IRA%20accounts%20allow%20employees%20to%20save%20and%20invest%20money%20that%20they%20make%20throughout%20their%20career%2C%20usually%20by%20depositing%20a%20percentage%20of%20their%20regular%20paycheck%20directly%20into%20the%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20might%20also%20contribute%20to%20an%20employee's%20401(k)%2C%20but%20they%20are%20under%20no%20federal%20requirement%20to%20do%20so.%20The%20retirement%20accounts%20an%20employee%20has%20access%20to%20and%20what%20benefits%20they%20retain%20after%20they%20stop%20work%20all%20depend%20on%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fretirement-plans-small-business-owners-financial-planner-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20package%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20individual%20company%20offers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkey-takeaways-blackrock-ceo-larry-finks-letter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20a%202024%20letter%20to%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20BlackRock%20CEO%20Larry%20Fink%20said%20the%20US%20retirement%20system%20puts%20undue%20pressure%20on%20employees%20to%20decide%20how%20much%20money%20to%20save%20and%20invest.%20With%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20many%20US%20cities%2C%20it%20can%20be%20difficult%20for%20Americans%20to%20predict%20how%20much%20money%20they%20are%20going%20to%20need%2C%20an%20issue%20Fink%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%20math%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-benefits-republicans-raise-age-retirement-cuts-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20comes%20into%20play%20when%20Americans%20retire%2C%20providing%20monthly%20government%20income%20benefits%20based%20on%20an%20individual's%20reported%20earnings.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20insurance%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20funded%20by%20taxes%20and%20provides%20income%20to%20retirees%20and%20workers%20with%20disabilities.%20Many%20retirees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-pensions-student-loan-debt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollect%20Social%20Security%20checks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20addition%20to%20living%20off%20their%20401(k)%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20fixed-income%20pensions%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-pensions-student-loan-debt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20longer%20a%20common%20company%20benefit%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20are%20still%20offered%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoney.usnews.com%2Fmoney%2Fretirement%2Fbaby-boomers%2Farticles%2Fjobs-that-still-offer-traditional-pensions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eselect%20government%20and%20public%20service%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Australia%2C%20however%2C%20companies%20are%20legally%20required%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ato.gov.au%2Fbusinesses-and-organisations%2Fsuper-for-employers%2Fpaying-super-contributions%2Fhow-much-super-to-pay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtribute%2011%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20an%20employee's%20monthly%20paycheck%20into%20their%20retirement%20account.%20This%20money%20can%20go%20into%20stocks%2C%20property%2C%20cash%2C%20or%20bonds%20%E2%80%94%20the%20employee%20has%20a%20choice.%20Employees%20can%20also%20contribute%20money%2C%20but%20much%20of%20the%20savings%20responsibility%20falls%20on%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20employer%20contribution%20amount%20is%20set%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.industrysuper.com%2Funderstand-super%2Fsuper-changes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincrease%20to%2012%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20they%20reach%20retirement%20age%2C%20which%20is%20between%2055%20and%2060%2C%20depending%20on%20birth%20year%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAustralians%20can%20access%20the%20fund%20with%20their%20savings%20and%20investment%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20does%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20because%20everybody%20is%20put%20into%20a%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20Reilly%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Australians%20have%20more%20choice%20in%20where%20and%20how%20their%20retirement%20money%20is%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Reilly%20explained%2C%20superannuation%20also%20allows%20retirees%20to%20access%20their%20money%20all%20in%20one%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20differs%20from%20the%20American%20system%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-saving-too-much-for-retirement-2024-04%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirees'%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20often%20held%20between%20a%20401(k)%2C%20other%20accounts%2C%20and%20outside%20investments.%20If%20an%20American%20employee%20works%20at%20multiple%20different%20companies%20during%20their%20career%2C%20Reilly%20said%20it%20can%20also%20complicate%20their%20retirement%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Australian%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.servicesaustralia.gov.au%2Fwho-can-get-age-pension%3Fcontext%3D22526%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eage%20pensions%3C%2Fa%3E%20aren't%20the%20same%20as%20Social%20Security.%20Retirees%20must%20meet%20a%20low%20enough%20asset%20criteria%20to%20access%20the%20age%20pension.%20Reilly%20said%20the%20more%20limited%20pension%20might%20be%20a%20disadvantage%20of%20the%20Australian%20system%20because%20many%20people's%20retirement%20is%20almost%20entirely%20dependent%20on%20their%20superannuation%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIf%20the%20US%20adopted%20superannuation%2C%20it%20could%20impact%20employee%20salaries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20Australian%20government%20sets%20the%20terms%20for%20superannuation%2C%20it%20is%20managed%20by%20the%20private%20sector.%20Employers%20manage%20the%20retirement%20funds%20for%20their%20employees%20without%20much%20political%20oversight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20America%20adopted%20superannuation%2C%20Reilly%20expects%20the%20system%20would%20work%20similarly%20%E2%80%94%20the%20federal%20government%20could%20establish%20what%20percentage%20of%20an%20employee's%20income%20employers%20need%20to%20contribute%2C%20but%20then%20companies%20could%20organize%20the%20retirement%20funds%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20pointed%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adp.com%2Fresources%2Farticles-and-insights%2Farticles%2Fp%2Fpooled-employer-plans.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20pooled-employer%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20retirement%20fund%20strategy%20that%20is%20already%20being%20tried%20in%20the%20US%2C%20allowing%20multiple%20companies%20to%20contribute%20to%20a%20single%20retirement%20fund%20for%20an%20employee%20if%20that%20person%20chooses%20to%20work%20at%20different%20companies%20throughout%20their%20career.%20Some%20individual%20states%2C%20such%20as%20California%20and%20Colorado%2C%20also%20require%20that%20employees%20are%20automatically%20enrolled%20in%20some%20kind%20of%20retirement%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20US%2C%20the%20infrastructure%20for%20having%20the%20private%20sector%20manage%20these%20funds%20%E2%80%94%20that%20all%20exists%20already%2C%26quot%3B%20Reilly%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20that%20would%20be%20a%20sensible%20way%20to%20do%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Reilly%20cautioned%20that%20applying%20Australia's%20retirement%20system%20to%20the%20US%20could%20negatively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-good-high-paying-jobs-america-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaffect%20employee%20wages%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Because%2C%20for%20companies%2C%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bvery%20unpopular%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20company%20hires%20someone%20new%2C%20she%20said%20they%20consider%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20employing%20that%20person.%20This%20includes%20salary%2C%20bonuses%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-must-have-employee-benefits-business-owners-should-offer-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebenefits%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20US%20employers%20become%20legally%20required%20to%20contribute%20to%20retirement%20funds%2C%20Reilly%20said%20companies%20may%20lower%20their%20employees'%20salaries%20to%20offset%20this%20new%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20system%20like%20superannuation%20could%20help%20ensure%20a%20retirement%20fund%20for%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewtrusts.org%2Fen%2Fabout%2Fnews-room%2Fopinion%2F2024%2F01%2F18%2Famerica-has-a-retirement-crisis-we-need-to-make-it-easier-to-save%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520vast%2520majority%2520of%2520retirement%2Cturn%252C%2520reduces%2520their%2520retirement%2520income.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2056%20million%20private%20sector%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20don't%20have%20retirement%20benefits%20through%20their%20employer%2C%20The%20Pew%20Charitable%20Trust%20reported%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20an%20American%20or%20an%20Australian%20thinking%20about%20retirement%3F%20Are%20you%20open%20to%20sharing%20details%20about%20how%20much%20you%20have%20saved%20and%20your%20savings%20strategy%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3A%2520allisonkelly%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eallisonkelly%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-make-us-retirement-system-better-australia-superannuation-benefits-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713261781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6618143c1caec1275a6f2f6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-make-us-retirement-system-better-australia-superannuation-benefits-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Austra