0who%20in%201984%20asked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fhistory%2Fspace-station-20th-historical-origins-of-iss%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENASA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Bpermanently%20manned%20space%20station%26quot%3B%20that%20other%20countries%20would%20be%20invited%20to%20contribute%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201988%2C%2015%20nations%20had%20agreed%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20project%2C%20then%20known%20as%20Space%20Station%20Freedom.%20Representatives%20from%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20nine%20members%20of%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20(ESA)%20signed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fhistory%2F20-years-ago-station-partners-sign-intergovernmental-agreement-iga%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInter-Governmental%20Agreement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(IGA)%20to%20consent%20to%20its%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%201991%2C%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%20invited%20newly-formed%20Russia%20to%20join%20the%20project%2C%20which%20changed%20its%20name%20to%20the%20ISS%20in%201993.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224764%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22soyuz%2011%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6618fa8016bde8d4ead832ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223573%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20crew%20of%20Soyuz%2011.%3Cp%3EKeystone%2FHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Soviets%20had%20long-standing%20expertise%20in%20aerospace%20technology%2C%20having%20launched%20the%20world's%20first%20space%20station%2C%20%26quot%3BSalyut%2C%26quot%3B%20in%201971.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20officially%20joining%2C%20Russia%20has%20worked%20extremely%20closely%20with%20the%20US%20on%20the%20ISS.%20Crew%20from%20both%20countries%20were%20part%20of%20the%20first%20monthlong%20expedition%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Astronauts%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6617c7533f923f7dab06b193%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETerry%20Virts%20of%20NASA%20and%20Anton%20Shkaplerov%20of%20Roscomos%20pose%20on%20October%208%2C%202015%20in%20Milan%2C%20Italy.%3Cp%3EPier%20Marco%20Tacca%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20ISS%2C%20for%20so%20long%20a%20place%20symbolizing%20the%20unity%20between%20nations%2C%20has%20begun%20to%20fall%20prey%20to%20political%20divisions%20as%20the%20era%20of%20post-Cold%20War%20optimism%20gave%20way%20to%20renewed%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202022%2C%20Russian%20cosmonauts%20on%20the%20ISS%20unveiled%20a%20flag%20of%20the%20Luhansk%20region%20in%20Ukraine.%20The%20region%20has%20recently%20been%20occupied%20by%20Russia's%20invading%20military%2C%20and%20the%20picture%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20show%20of%20support%20for%20Putin's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20outrageous%20provocation%20at%20a%20site%20where%20political%20differences%20were%20supposed%20to%20matter%20less%20than%20the%20common%20pursuit%20of%20truth%2C%20said%20critics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20incredibly%20disappointed%20to%20see%20cosmonauts%20and%20Roscosmos%20using%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2F16748-international-space-station.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInternational%20Space%20Station%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20platform%20to%20promote%20their%20illegal%20and%20immoral%20war%2C%20where%20civilians%20are%20being%20killed%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Terry%20Virts%2C%20a%20US%20astronaut%20and%20commander%20of%20the%20ISS%20in%202015%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Frussia-cosmonauts-ukraine-luhansk-propaganda%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222044%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22three%20cosmonauts%20pose%20with%20blue%20and%20red%20striped%20flag%20inside%20space%20station%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6618fb871caec1275a6f67e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20cosmonauts%20Oleg%20Artemyev%2C%20Denis%20Matveev%20and%20Sergey%20Korsakov%20pose%20with%20a%20flag%20of%20the%20self-proclaimed%20Luhansk%20People's%20Republic%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20in%20this%20picture%20released%20July%204%2C%202022.%3Cp%3ERoscosmos%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Virts%20told%20BI%20that%20Russia's%20economic%20difficulties%20mean%20that%2C%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20its%20provocations%20are%20unlikely%20to%20be%20a%20prelude%20to%20fully%20withdrawing%20from%20the%20ISS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20only%20viable%20civilian%20space%20activity%20for%20them%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20channeling%20huge%20amounts%20of%20money%20into%20its%20Ukraine%20campaign%2C%20with%20military%20spending%20accounting%20for%206%25%20of%20GDP%20last%20year.%20It%20leaves%20little%20left%20over%20for%20a%20huge%20and%20ambitious%20project%20such%20as%20building%20a%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20economy%20has%20been%20transitioned%20to%20a%20war%20footing%20and%20they%20will%20not%20have%20the%20money%20to%20begin%20any%20new%20space%20exploration%20initiatives%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Virts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUS%20reliance%20on%20Russia%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20ISS%20agreement%2C%20every%20nation%20taking%20part%20helps%20fund%20it.%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%2C%20as%20the%20world's%20space%20exploration%20superpowers%2C%20take%20the%20largest%20share%20of%20responsibility%20for%20maintaining%20the%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ISS's%20habitable%20modules%2C%20where%20the%20astronauts%20live%20and%20work%2C%20are%20jointly%20owned%20by%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20and%20physically%20connected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ISS%20crew%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6618fcac16bde8d4ead832fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPilot%20Michael%20Barratt%2C%20commander%20Matthew%20Dominick%2C%20Russian%20cosmonaut%20and%20mission%20specialist%20Alexander%20Grebenkin%2C%20and%20mission%20specialist%20Jeanette%20Epps%20in%20March%202024%20before%20a%20six-month%20ISS%20mission.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStuart%2C%20of%20Imperial%20College%2C%20said%20that%20the%20way%20the%20station%20is%20built%20enforces%20cooperation%20between%20nations%20that%20find%20little%20else%20to%20agree%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20strong%20words%20have%20been%20used%20on%20both%20sides%20since%20the%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20the%20agencies%20involved%20in%20the%20station%E2%80%94as%20well%20as%20the%20hardware%20of%20the%20station%20itself%E2%80%94are%20interdependent%20in%20a%20way%20that%20has%20so%20far%20ensured%20a%20stable%2C%20if%20tense%2C%20continuation%20of%20operation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stuart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20decades%20of%20operation%2C%20other%20political%20tensions%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20have%20led%20to%20questions%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20ISS%2C%20but%20it%20has%20always%20weathered%20the%20storm%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stuart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20future%20of%20the%20ISS%2C%20if%20Russia%20does%20act%20on%20its%20threats%20and%20withdraws%2C%20appears%20bleak.%20It%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20get%20the%20ISS%20to%20even%20move%20without%20Russian%20help%2C%20said%20Virts.%20And%20transporting%20astronauts%20to%20the%20station%20would%20be%20more%20difficult%2C%20as%20under