rt%2C%20Target%2C%20and%20other%20chains's%20own%20policies%20and%20practices%20could%20be%20worsening%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFrom%20conflicting%20policies%20to%20understaffing%2C%20retailers%20can%20make%20it%20hard%20for%20workers%20to%20prevent%20theft.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20retail%20industry%20has%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20past%20year%20raising%20alarms%20around%20shoplifting%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-major-retailers-are-beating-rise-in-retail-theft-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganized%20retail%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20conversations%20around%20the%20problem%20of%20theft%20at%20stores%20often%20centers%20around%20external%20factors%20like%20law%20enforcement%20and%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20obstacles%20to%20curtailing%20theft%20might%20be%20a%20lot%20closer%20to%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20major%20retailers%2C%20including%20Walmart%2C%20Target%2C%20and%20others%2C%20have%20policies%20that%20sometimes%20prevent%20their%20own%20staff%20from%20addressing%20shoplifting%20at%20their%20stores%2C%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20have%20been%20disciplined%20or%20fired%20if%20they%20go%20after%20shoplifters%2C%20according%20to%20interviews%20and%20media%20reports.%20Others%20say%20a%20lack%20of%20resources%20and%20follow-up%20after%20the%20fact%20also%20makes%20it%20more%20logical%20for%20the%20workers%20to%20just%20turn%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20the%20problem%20rather%20than%20do%20anything%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMost%20retailers%20have%20policies%20preventing%20employees%20from%20taking%20action%20when%20theft%20happens%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERhea%20Gordon%2C%20a%20former%20Walmart%20associate%20at%20one%20of%20the%20retailer's%20stores%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-worker-fired-shoplifters-retail-theft-fight-problems-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshe%20was%20fired%20after%20trying%20to%20catch%20two%20shoplifters%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20were%20taking%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20worth%20of%20makeup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20hand%2C%20Gordon%20said%2C%20managers%20told%20her%20and%20other%20employees%20to%20check%20shopping%20baskets%2C%20bags%2C%20and%20other%20areas%20where%20customers%20could%20hide%20unpaid%20merchandise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%2C%20associates%20are%20frequently%20told%20not%20to%20engage%20with%20customers%20who%20resist%20or%20who%20make%20threats%20after%20employees%20approach%20them.%20Walmart's%20Customer%20Theft%20policy%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20repeatedly%20tells%20associates%20%26quot%3Bto%20disengage%20and%20withdraw%20from%20the%20situation%26quot%3B%20and%20contact%20law%20enforcement%20if%20the%20situation%20becomes%20at%20all%20heated%2C%20according%20to%20a%20copy%20reviewed%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAssociate%20safety%20is%20always%20a%20top%20priority%20and%20we%20have%20policies%20in%20place%20to%20protect%20the%20health%20and%20wellbeing%20of%20those%20in%20our%20stores%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Walmart%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDollar%20General's%20employee%20handbook%20takes%20a%20similarly%20hands-off%20approach.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20suspect%20that%20someone%20is%20shoplifting%2C%20you%20should%20provide%20them%20with%20good%20customer%20service%20as%20you%20would%20any%20other%20customer%20and%20inform%20the%20manager%20on%20duty%20of%20your%20observations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20handbook%20reads.%20%26quot%3BStore%20employees%20must%20never%20become%20involved%20in%20physical%20or%20verbal%20confrontations%20or%20touch%20a%20customer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Dollar%20General%20spokesperson%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20prioritize%20employee%20and%20customer%20safety%20over%20the%20potential%20loss%20of%20merchandise.%20For%20that%20reason%2C%20employees%20are%20instructed%20not%20to%20place%20themselves%20or%20others%20in%20danger%20in%20order%20to%20prevent%20shoplifting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELululemon%20also%20made%20news%20when%20it%20fired%20several%20workers%20who%20had%20attempted%20to%20intervene%20with%20suspected%20shoplifters.%20CEO%20Calvin%20McDonald%20cited%20safety%20concerns%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20company's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-lululemon-fire-employees-who-stop-theft-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20zero-tolerance%20policy%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20telling%20CNBC%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20only%20merchandise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20your%20job%20is%20actually%20in%20security%2C%20your%20hands%20are%20metaphorically%20tied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20summer%20at%20a%20grocery%20store%20in%20Colorado%2C%20security%20worker%20Santino%20Burrola%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrocery-security-worker-lost-job-after-viral-video-of-theft-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efired%20after%20he%20followed%20and%20filmed%20a%20group%20of%20suspected%20shoplifters%3C%2Fa%3E%20loading%20a%20cart%20full%20of%20merchandise%20into%20a%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Target%20worker%20in%20California%20told%20BI%20his%20location%20sees%20multiple%20instances%20of%20theft%20per%20day%2C%20with%20the%20company's%20Assets%20Protection%20employees%20giving%20chase%20%E2%80%94%20but%20usually%20unable%20to%20do%20anything%20to%20stop%20the%20theft%20or%20get%20information%20that%20could%20curb%20future%20thefts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20policy%20is%20not%20to%20touch%20them%20but%20just%20ask%20them%20to%20please%20don't%20steal%20from%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20worker%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20make%20it%20to%20the%20sidewalk%2C%20then%20they%20are%20scot-free.%26quot%3B%20Target%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20former%20Walmart%20employees%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20retailer's%20asset%20protection%20teams%20are%20tasked%20with%20observing%20and%20reporting%20possible%20crimes%2C%20but%20are%20otherwise%20instructed%20to%20not%20reveal%20themselves%20or%20their%20role%20to%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERetailers%20don't%20always%20hire%20enough%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20or%20give%20them%20the%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20to%20prevent%20theft%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20policies%20that%20hold%20employees%20back.%20At%20some%20stores%2C%20workers%20just%20don't%20have%20the%20resources%20to%20prevent%20theft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Walmart%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20associates%20who%20monitor%20self-checkout%20are%20supposed%20to%20conduct%20random%20%26quot%3Bcart%20checks%26quot%3B%20of%20Spark%20drivers%20who%20shop%20an%20order%20before%20delivering%20it.%20The%20process%20involves%20the%20associate%20scanning%20a%20few%20items%20using%20a%20phone%20app%20before%20allowing%20the%20Spark%20driver%20to%20exit%20the%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20contractor%20who%20shops%20and%20delivers%20for%20Walmart's%20Spark%20delivery%20service%20in%20Montana%20told%20BI%20that%20associates%20at%20his%20store%20don't%20have%20a%20phone%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20check%20%26quot%3Bnine%20times%20out%20of%2010.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20that%20happens%2C%20associates%20direct%20him%20to%20ignore%20the%20cart%20check%20notification%20on%20his%20own%20phone%2C%20telling%20him%20that%20it%20will%20%26quot%3Btime%20out%26quot%3B%20eventually%2C%20the%20driver%20said.%20%26quot%3BWalmart%20has%20a%20system%20that%20doesn't%20work%20because%20Walmart%20doesn't%20provide%20them%20the%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20driver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20an%20electronics%20department%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20driver%20added.%20%26quot%3BGo%20get%20a%20phone%2C%20they're%20right%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Walmart%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20that%20the%20retailer%20conducts%20cart%20checks%20but%20didn't%20comment%20on%20the%20lack%20of%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20another%20seemingly%20chronic%20issue%3A%20companies%20just%20aren't%20hiring%20enough%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20pandemic%20turnover%20and%20rising%20wages%20have%20been%20challenges%2C%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-labor-shortage-understaffing-hiring-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretailers%20have%20understaffed%20their%20stores%20for%20years.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-general-workers-hours-cut-employee-shortage-leads-to-clutter-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDollar%20General%20often%20operates%20stores%20with%20as%20few%20as%20one%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20there's%20one%20person%20for%20a%20store%20that%20is%20thousands%20of%20square%20feet%2C%20how%20much%20is%20one%20human%20being%20going%20to%20do%3F%26quot%3B%20Thea%20Sebastian%2C%20director%20at%20the%20Futures%20Institute%2C%20told%20BI.%20Sebastian%20and%20Hanna%20Love%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20Brookings%2C%20co-authored%20a%20recent%20study%20that%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-we-dont-actually-know-whether-retail-theft-big-problem-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretail%20theft%20is%20hard%20to%20quantify%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20frequently%20overstated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20report's%20recommendations%20for%20retailers%3A%20Hire%20enough%20employees%20at%20stores%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20they%20aren't%20constantly%20overworked.%20%26quot%3BA%20happy%20worker%20is%20going%20to%20make%20for%20a%20much%20happier%20customer%2C%20who%20then%20is%20going%20to%20be%20much%20less%20likely%20to%20engage%20in%20these%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20Sebastian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20happy%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20and%20enough%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20effective%20in%20reducing%20crime%2C%20it%20will%20just%20help%20improve%20the%20customer%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Love%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWho%20wants%20to%20go%20into%20a%20store%20when%20everything's%20already%20behind%20the%20glass%2C%20you%20can't%20find%20a%20person%20to%20open%20it%20for%20you%2C%20and%20you%20just%20walk%20out%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20at%20Walmart%2C%20Target%2C%20or%20another%20major%20retailer%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20these%20reporters%20at%20dreuter%40businessinsider.com%20or%20abitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshoplifting-biggest-enablers-might-be-retailers-themselves-walmart-target-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713259021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cfb3926fcb546d2d50e9dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshoplifting-biggest-enablers-might-be-retailers-themselves-walmart-target-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Retailers%20keep%20talking%20about%20the%20scourge%20of%20shoplifting.%20But%20their%20own%20staffing%20shortages%20and%20policies%20might%20be%20the%20source%20of%20many%20of%20their%20problems.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter%2CDominick%20Reuter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshoplifting-biggest-enablers-might-be-retailers-themselves-walmart-target-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BFat%20Free%20At%2043%26quot%3B%3A%20Author%20Ankur%20Warikoo%20Shares%20His%20Weight%20Loss%20Journey%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAnkur%20Warikoo%2C%20a%20well-known%20author%2