%20seeds%2C%20soak%20them%20for%20germination.%20But%20this%20process%20is%20required%20only%20in%20big%20seeds%20like%20cardamom%20and%20coriander.%20You%20can%20soak%20them%20overnight%20before%20sowing.%20This%20process%20is%20not%20required%20in%20small%20seeds%20like%20cumin%2C%20fennel%2C%20and%20mustard%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20further%2C%20Dr%20Anshu%20says%20the%20germination%20period%20varies%20as%20per%20spices.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20fennel%20takes%207%20to%2015%20days%2C%20cumin%20takes%2045%20days%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F240539%2Fhow-to-grow-coriander-without-seeds-market-roots-time-method-simple-terrace-balcony-homegrown-ludhiana-mona-chopra-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoriander%20seeds%20%3C%2Fa%3Erequire%2015%20days%2C%20and%20fenugreek%20can%20germinate%20in%20just%20three%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC1_pLZuscDO%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC1_pLZuscDO%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC1_pLZuscDO%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20%F0%9F%A6%8BDr.%20Rathi%20Anshu%20%2F%20Sustainability%2FPlant%20care%20tips%20%2C%20DIY%2C%20Decor%20(%40myplantsmygarden)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20seeds%20must%20be%20sown%20in%20small%20cups.%20After%20germination%2C%20transfer%20the%20plant%20into%20big%20pots%20of%20say%2012%20inches.%20Keep%20it%20in%20a%20semi-shade%20for%20about%20a%20week%20and%20then%20place%20them%20under%20direct%20sunlight%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETest%20the%20soil%20using%20this%20DIY%20hack%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Anshu%20suggests%20a%20sandy%20soil%20to%20cultivate%20spices.%20Because%20of%20the%20geography%20of%20her%20city%2C%20which%20is%20located%20between%20the%20rivers%20Ganges%20and%20Yamuna%2C%20she%20is%20blessed%20with%20a%20sandy%20porous%20soil.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20I%20do%20not%20require%20to%20bother%20about%20the%20soil%20composition.%20However%2C%20for%20gardeners%20in%20other%20regions%20you%20need%20to%20test%20your%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20advises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%2C%20she%20recommends%20a%20DIY%20trick%20to%20test%20the%20soil%20consistency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTake%20a%20handful%20of%20soil%2C%20dampen%20it%2C%20and%20try%20to%20shape%20it%20into%20a%20%3Cem%3Eladdu%3C%2Fem%3E.%20If%20you%20can%20easily%20make%20%3Cem%3Eladdu%20%3C%2Fem%3Efrom%20the%20soil%2C%20it%20has%20a%20high%20clay%20content.%20Mix%2020%20to%2030%20percent%20of%20sand%20into%20the%20soil%20till%20it%20crumbles%20and%20falls%20apart.%20Additionally%2C%20also%20mix%2020%20to%2030%20percent%20of%20cow%20dung%20compost%20and%20a%20handful%20of%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%20%3C%2Fem%3E(cake)%20powder%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Anshu%20suggests%20a%20sandy%20soil%20to%20cultivate%20spices%20like%20bay%20leaf%20and%20saffron.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347220%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Anshu%20suggests%20a%20sandy%20soil%20to%20cultivate%20spices%20like%20bay%20leaf%20and%20saffron.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EKnow%20when%20to%20fertilise%20the%20plant%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20have%20already%20added%20cow%20dung%20compost%20and%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%20%3C%2Fem%3Einto%20the%20soil%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20need%20to%20fertilise%20the%20soil%20frequently.%20Right%20before%2015%20days%20of%20flowering%20season%2C%20add%20a%20handful%20of%20vermicompost%20in%20the%20pot%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHarvest%20spices%20at%20the%20right%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Anshu%20says%20different%20spices%20have%20varied%20stages%20of%20flowering%20and%20production.%20%E2%80%9CFor